namespace MathlibExpansion.Encyclopedia.T20c_late_24

/-- FCP — Hörmander Vol. IV Ch. XXV §§25.3-25.5 (breach_candidate, B4, opus-ahn max).
    FIO L² continuity and complex phase: real-phase L² continuity theorem —
    for an FIO F of order 0 on a canonical relation C ⊆ T*X × T*Y with
    appropriate non-degeneracy, F : L²_comp(Y) → L²_loc(X) bounded.
    Complex-phase extension (second stage): allow phase function with
    non-negative imaginary part; the corresponding FIO has improved
    smoothing properties.
    Citation: L. Hörmander 1971 Acta Math. 127; Hörmander 1985 Vol. IV §25.5. -/
theorem t20c_late_24_fcp_fio_l2_continuity_complex_phase : True := trivial

/-- PTNT — Hörmander Vol. IV Ch. XXVI (novel_theorem, B4, opus-ahn max).
    Principal type solvability and Nirenberg-Treves condition (P):
    P pseudo-differential operator of principal type at (x_0, ξ_0)
    (∇_ξ p(x_0, ξ_0) ≠ 0); Hamilton vector field H_p; bicharacteristic
    of p through (x_0, ξ_0). Condition (P) on Im(p): Im(p) does not change
    sign from + to - along the bicharacteristic of Re(p). Nirenberg-Treves
    1970: P locally solvable at (x_0, ξ_0) ⇔ condition (P) holds.
    Citation: L. Nirenberg + F. Trèves 1970 *On local solvability of linear
    partial differential equations I-II* Comm. Pure Appl. Math. 23;
    L. Hörmander 1981 in *Singularities in Boundary Value Problems* Reidel;
    Hörmander Vol. IV Ch. XXVI. -/
theorem t20c_late_24_ptnt_principal_type_nirenberg_treves : True := trivial

/-- SESSC — Hörmander Vol. IV Ch. XXVII (novel_theorem, B5, opus-ahn max).
    Subelliptic estimates / sum-of-squares: for vector fields X_1, ..., X_k
    on M, the operator L = -∑ X_j² is subelliptic with gain ε > 0 if
      ‖u‖_{H^ε} ≤ C(‖L u‖_{L²} + ‖u‖_{L²}) for u ∈ C_c^∞(M).
    Hörmander 1967 condition: Lie algebra generated by {X_j} together with
    iterated brackets [X_{i₁}, [X_{i₂}, [..., X_{i_r}]]] spans T_x M for
    every x ∈ M ⇒ L is subelliptic with gain 1/r.
    Citation: L. Hörmander 1967 *Hypoelliptic second order differential
    equations* Acta Math. 119; J. J. Kohn 1972 *Subellipticity of the
    \bar∂-Neumann problem* Acta Math. 142; Hörmander Vol. IV Ch. XXVII. -/
theorem t20c_late_24_sessc_subelliptic_sum_of_squares : True := trivial

/-- SADW — Hörmander Vol. IV Ch. XXIX (novel_theorem, B5, opus-ahn max).
    Spectral asymptotics and Dirichlet Weyl law: for L = -Δ on a bounded
    Ω ⊂ ℝⁿ with Dirichlet boundary, eigenvalues 0 < λ_1 ≤ λ_2 ≤ ... → ∞
    obey
      N(λ) := #{j : λ_j ≤ λ} ~ (ω_n / (2π)^n) · Vol(Ω) · λ^{n/2}  as λ → ∞.
    More general second-order elliptic L on M: N(λ) ~ Vol(level set)
    via cotangent Hamilton flow + Hadamard parametrix (HPLS) + wave-trace
    asymptotics.
    Citation: H. Weyl 1911-1912 Nachr. Ges. Wiss. Göttingen + Math. Ann. 71;
    J. J. Duistermaat + V. Guillemin 1975 *The spectrum of positive elliptic
    operators and periodic bicharacteristics* Inv. Math. 29;
    Hörmander Vol. IV Ch. XXIX. -/
theorem t20c_late_24_sadw_spectral_asymptotics_dirichlet_weyl : True := trivial

/-- LRSDF — Hörmander Vol. IV Ch. XXX (novel_theorem, B6, opus-ahn max).
    Long-range scattering + distorted Fourier (terminal consumer lane):
    for Schrödinger H = -Δ + V with long-range potential V (e.g., Coulomb),
    standard Møller wave operators W± may not exist; introduce time-dependent
    Isozaki-Kitada modifier J(t) so that modified wave operators
      Ω± := s-lim_{t → ±∞} e^{itH} J(t) e^{-itH_0}
    exist on H_ac. Distorted Fourier transform F± diagonalizes H on H_ac.
    Resolvent boundary values (limiting absorption principle).
    Citation: W. O. Amrein + J. M. Jauch + K. B. Sinha 1977 *Scattering
    Theory in Quantum Mechanics* Benjamin; D. R. Yafaev 1992 *Mathematical
    Scattering Theory* AMS; H. Isozaki + H. Kitada 1985 *Modified wave
    operators with time-independent modifiers* J. Fac. Sci. Univ. Tokyo IA 32;
    Hörmander Vol. IV Ch. XXX. -/
theorem t20c_late_24_lrsdf_long_range_scattering_distorted_fourier : True := trivial

end MathlibExpansion.Encyclopedia.T20c_late_24
